headline.main: Philadelphia prepares for Pope's grand U.S. finale
headline.sub: Philadelphia prepares for Pope's grand U.S. finale

docs.snippet: Security is tight for Pope Francis' visit to Philadelphia where the pontiff will hold Mass for an anticipated 1.5 million people before wrapping up his U.S. tour. Linda So reports....

headline.main: As UN Peacekeeping Veers Toward Counterterror, US Steps In
headline.print_headline: As UN Peacekeeping Veers Toward Counterterror, US Steps In

docs.snippet: Along a quiet cease-fire line in Cyprus, U.N. peacekeepers handle an increasingly old-fashioned job: actually keeping the peace. The last deadly incident was in 1996. Today's challenges include keeping poachers and rogue farmers out of no man's la...
docs.lead_paragraph: Along a quiet cease-fire line in Cyprus, U.N. peacekeepers handle an increasingly old-fashioned job: actually keeping the peace. The last deadly incident was in 1996. Today's challenges include keeping poachers and rogue farmers out of no man's land. "Most of the time we don't wear weapons," said the force commander, Maj. Gen. Kristin Lund.
